  <description type="morphology">Flowering stems erect, 1.5–5 dm. Leaves alternate; blade elliptic-lanceolate, 4–8
        cm, margins not glandular, those of distal leaves irregularly serrate. Flowers: sepals
        linear to lanceolate, 3.5–4.5 mm, apex blunt; petals erect basally, widely spreading
        distally, yellow, oblong to elliptic-lanceolate, 7–9 mm, apex mucronate. Carpels connate
        basally, divergent in fruit.</description>
